Tomorrowland Drops Full Lineup for 'Around The World' 2021 Digital Festival

Earlier this month, we reported Tomorrowland released the first phase of artists for their upcoming digital festival. Today, the organizers revealed the entire lineup ahead of their Around The World virtual event. Trust us, it's everything and more that you could have hoped for!

If you haven't already purchased your tickets to join in the highly-anticipated celebration, you can do so here. On Friday, July 16, 2021, through Saturday, July 17, 2021, "the Magical Island Pāpiliōnem will welcome back the People of Tomorrow to the second edition of Tomorrowland – Around the World."

A couple of weeks ago, dedicated fans across the globe learned Armin van Buuren, Claptone, Nicky Romero and Adam Beyer would be unleashing special performances. Today, it's been revealed an additional 40+ artists have been added to the lineup to complete the bill. The stacked lineup is composed of a wide variety of genres, including techno, house, trance, big room, psy trance, and much more!

Ticketholders will be treated to soon-to-be legendary performances by Afrojack, Charlotte de Witte, Enrico Sanguiliano, Fedde Le Grand, Headhunterz, Hi-Lo, Lost Frequencies, QUINTINO, Robin Shulz, Tale Of Us, Vini Vici, Vintage Culture, and many more talented artists! Check out the full lineup below! Will you be attending?
